The paper deals with the problem of infrastructure inspection using UAVs, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of Lidars for navigation and planning algorithms, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The implementation of a supervisor to dictate switching between local navigation routines suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY). Lastly, the use of a planner to calculate the path along the bridge surface suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for optimization.
